This paper deals with image classification using both visual features and semantic keywords, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the focus on malicious crowd images and the use of keywords for classification suggest that this paper could also fit under computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of a dataset and evaluation metrics related to multimedia (cs.MM) also make this a possible sub-category.
